events.name: Oklahoma City Thunder at Charlotte Hornets

headlines.description: — LaMelo Ball had 27 points, 10 rebounds and nine assists and the Charlotte Hornets beat the Oklahoma City Thunder 121-113 on Thursday night for just their third victory in the last 14 games.
headlines.shortLinkText: LaMelo Ball has 27 points to help Hornets beat Thunder

headlines.shortLinkText: Haliburton, Hield combine for 11 3s, Pacers top Cavs 135-126

headlines.description: — Even from atop the NBA standings, the Boston Celtics remember the losses.
headlines.shortLinkText: Tatum, Brown score 29 each and Celtics beat Clippers 116-110

headlines.description: — Ja Morant had a career-high 17 assists and scored 19 points and the Memphis Grizzlies won for the first time in three games, beating the struggling Toronto Raptors 119-106 on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Morant has career-high 17 assists, Grizzlies rout Raptors

events.name: New York Knicks at San Antonio Spurs

headlines.description: — Julius Randle bullied San Antonio, but the Spurs never backed down.
headlines.shortLinkText: Spurs overcome Randle's 41, hand Knicks fifth straight loss

headlines.description: — Luka Doncic followed his 60-point triple-double two nights earlier with 35 points in his NBA-best eighth triple-double of the season, and the Dallas Mavericks beat the Houston Rockets 129-114 on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Doncic has another triple-double, Mavs beat Rockets 129-114
